        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 6:36PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 636 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Morris Chapel, or 7 miles north of Savannah, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Savannah, Olive Hill, Morris Chapel, Crump, Saltillo, Milledgeville,
Thurman, Right, Sibley, Phillips, Hinkle, Five Forks, Pleasant Grove,
Bath Springs, Swift, Olivehill, Bucktown, Cerro Gordo, and Coffee
Landing.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
